ore","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that one should be aware of."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Store-internals-rewrite","text":"Store internals rewrite"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The store’s internals have been rewritten to improved performance and to pave the way for future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features. While this should not be a breaking change, with any rewrite it is important to thoroughly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test your application after upgrading."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"StateObject-compatibility","text":"StateObject compatibility"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":" allow a view to own a value or object over time, ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when a parent view is recomputed, the view-local state isn’t recreated from scratch."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One important difference between "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is that "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"eager, while "},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s is lazy. Because of this, if you initialize a root "},{"code":"Store","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to be held"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", stores will be initialized (and immediately discarded) whenever the parent view’s body"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is computed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":